main event: On May 1957, four objects were observed, with three objects being the size of a pixel and one object being 1/5 the size of a pixel. The objects were white and their lights appeared in an irregular path from 10 to 30 seconds before disappearing in different directions.
interesting points: The sighting involved four objects, three of which were of similar size and one significantly smaller.
The lights on the objects followed an irregular path before disappearing in different directions.
One object appeared 30 seconds after the first three objects, then disappeared in the North.
The conclusion included possibilities of the objects being a missile, balloon, aircraft, astronomical, or unknown.
The report mentions that the sighting was not confirmed by radar.
sighted object: Four white objects with irregular lights
witnesses: Capt. Lawrence Stage Jr. and others
